# __title__ adapter

Generated by `crafted-design scaffold adapter __id__`. Maps the editor's
canonical components onto the __title__ design system.

## Wiring it up

Add a side-effect import **before** you render `<Editor />`:

```ts
import './__id__' // this folder's index.ts
```

The **__title__** entry then appears in the adapter switcher. To pin it (and
hide the switcher), pass it to the editor:

```tsx
<Editor adapter="__id__" />
```

## Status

The skeleton wires `box` and `button`. The registry has **48** canonicals —
implement the rest in `components/` and add them to the `components` map in
`index.ts`. Any canonical without an impl renders a placeholder in the canvas,
so you can ship incrementally.

See the authoring walkthrough in the docs (`TUTORIAL_ADAPTER`) for the full
`AdapterRenderProps` contract and the per-canonical prop shapes
(`@crafted-design/editor/sdk` exports a `*Props` type for each).
